title.narrative: National capacity to apply child- friendly proceedings, alternatives to detention and diversion in line with international norms isenhanced.

description.narrative: Building on previous experience, UNICEF Morocco continued building the capacities of justice professionals and law enforcement services, resulting in decrease by 30 percent of deprivation of liberty for children in conflict with the law (since 2017) and increase of proportion of children benefiting from alternative to detention by 5 points compare to the previous year. UNICEF Morocco accompaniment of justice’ reform reinforced access of victims of violence to child friendly justice and making use of referral networks and collaboration with other sectors, including social welfare, at provincial level. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:14/01/2022
